Next, we open the input file using an ifstream object. We then use a while loop to read each line of the file using getline(). Inside the loop, we split each line into individual words using a do-while loop and a string::find() method. We then iterate over each word and increment count if it matches our target word.

Finally, we close the input file and print out the final count. Note that this program assumes that the target word is on a single line and does not support more complex patterns or regular expressions.

